nova/conf/libvirt.py.message:
I agree with everything Adam says above. That's not surprising considering I was heavily involved in coming up with it in the first place; but Alex & Stephen's comments didn't change my mind at all.

@Alex: We're enabling the *capability* by default, but as Adam says, you have to ask for the feature explicitly to get it on your VM. Enabling the capability costs us nothing.

@Stephen: We do auto-detect that the feature itself is present. The only thing we can't always auto-detect is the limit. When that's the case, assuming 'unlimited' is the reasonable thing. There's nothing to say we'll bounce on a SEV slot limit rather than e.g. a RAM limit as Adam suggests. This is kind of like the fact that we don't try to limit the number of neutron ports you can get based on the system's total bandwidth capability (until bw qos). Absent an actual resource we can track, we have no choice but to treat it as unlimited.

More I could say, but Adam said most of it already. Hope this is convincing enough.

